value: Breeds on the coasts and islands of Bering Sea and adjacent parts of the Arctic and North Pacific Oceans from Koliuchin Island and Cape Lisburne south to the Kurile and Commander Islands on the west and to Forrester Island, Alaska, on the east. Winters from the Commander, and Aleutian Islands south to Hondo and the Queen Charlotte Islands.
refer: Peter's Checklist of the Birds of the World

value: Mostly pelagic; nests on rocky islands in cliff crevices and among boulders, rarely in ground burrows.
